{"id":868,"category_slug":"ielts-listening","category_name":"IELTS Listening","position":229,"title":"Cam6 - Test 2 - Part 1","subtitle":"Children's Art Workshops Info","level":"B1","parts":72,"url":"https://dailydictation.com/exercises/ielts-listening/cam6-test-2-part-1.868/listen-and-type","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-6-test-2-part-1-2023-08-02-09-32-11/0-ielts-cambridge-6-test-2-part-1.mp3","transcript":"Good morning, Synmouth Museum. Can I help you?\nOh yes. Good morning.\nI'm interested in the children's workshops and I'd like a little more information, please.\nDo you mean the Art and Craft workshops?\nYes. A friend of a friend mentioned them -\nthe children do painting and make models and so forth.\nYes, of course.\nUm, where to begin?\nFirst of all, as you probably know, they run every Saturday.\nFine. And what about ages?\nWell, all ages from five upwards are welcome,\nthough we do ask that children below eight years of age are accompanied by an adult.\nFine. That wouldn't be a problem.\nWhat about cost?\nWell, I think you'll find them very reasonable.\nIt's £2.50 a child,\nwith 80 pence off for two or more children from the same family.\nOh yes, very reasonable.\nAnd are they held in the main museum?\nNot exactly.\nThey're nearby.\nCould you give me the full address?\nI don't know the area very well.\nYes, it's Winter House.\nRight.\nAnd that's in Tamer Street.\nCould you spell that please?\nYes, TAMER Street.\nLovely.\nAnd I do need to tell you that there's a security entrance,\nso you need to press the green button for someone to let you in.\nDon't press the red button please,\nbut don't worry, it's all clearly labelled.\nOkay. And one more question -\nis parking available nearby?\nWe're driving in from out of town.\nYour best bet is to leave your car at the back of the library -\non a Saturday morning, there are plenty of spaces there.\nIt's right next door to the museum.\nAnd can I ask about booking places?\nYes, and I must tell you, you really should book by calling the education department here.\nOh, I'm sorry, should I have rung them instead of the main museum number?\nNo, that's fine this time, please don't worry.\nBut for future reference, I'll give you the direct number.\nIt's 200765.\nGreat, I've got that.\nBut I'm very happy to give you information about the next two workshops.\nOn Saturday the 16th, there's Building Castles.\nOh, sounds great!\nThis involves quite a bit of glue, so just make sure the kids are in old clothes.\nI know, ones I don't mind getting mucky.\nExactly.\nAnd if possible, could you bring along bottle tops\nwhich the children might be able to use in the models, you know, as decoration?\nWe'll certainly try to find some for you.\nThen the following week...\nThat'll be the 23rd, won't it?\nYes, that's right.\nOn that day, it's what we call Undersea Worlds.\nThis is where they make scenes with fishes, underground caverns and so on.\nIs that likely to get very dirty?\nLots of paint splashes?\nNot really, so we don't recommend any special clothes for that one.\nBut if you could search out some silver paper to bring along to use in the sessions,\nyou know, it's shiny - it looks like water, that'd be great.\nYes, of course. We'll see what we can come up with.\nWell, thank you ever so much for all your help.\nThe sessions sound really good and I'll certainly book up for the next two.\nLovely.\nThanks very much for ringing.\nBye.\nBye-bye.","youtube_video_id":"","details_cached_at":"2026-06-15T20:51:25","challenges":[{"position":1,"content":"Good morning, Synmouth Museum. Can I help you?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-6-test-2-part-1-2023-08-02-09-32-11/1.mp3","time_start":0.49,"time_end":3.68},{"position":2,"content":"Oh yes. Good morning.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-6-test-2-part-1-2023-08-02-09-32-11/2.mp3","time_start":4.19,"time_end":6.5},{"position":3,"content":"I'm interested in the children's workshops and I'd like a little more information, please.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-6-test-2-part-1-2023-08-02-09-32-11/3.mp3","time_start":6.5,"time_end":11.17},{"position":4,"content":"Do you mean the Art and Craft workshops?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-6-test-2-part-1-2023-08-02-09-32-11/4.mp3","time_start":11.17,"time_end":13.79},{"position":5,"content":"Yes. A friend of a friend mentioned them -","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-6-test-2-part-1-2023-08-02-09-32-11/5.mp3","time_start":13.79,"time_end":16.41},{"position":6,"content":"the children do painting and make models and so forth.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-6-test-2-part-1-2023-08-02-09-32-11/6.mp3","time_start":16.41,"time_end":19.5},{"position":7,"content":"Yes, of course.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-6-test-2-part-1-2023-08-02-09-32-11/7.mp3","time_start":19.97,"time_end":21.35},{"position":8,"content":"Um, where to begin?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-6-test-2-part-1-2023-08-02-09-32-11/8.mp3","time_start":21.57,"time_end":24.02},{"position":9,"content":"First of all, as you probably know, they run every Saturday.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-6-test-2-part-1-2023-08-02-09-32-11/9.mp3","time_start":24.34,"time_end":28.62},{"position":10,"content":"Fine. And what about ages?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-6-test-2-part-1-2023-08-02-09-32-11/10.mp3","time_start":28.99,"time_end":31.76},{"position":11,"content":"Well, all ages from five upwards are welcome,","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-6-test-2-part-1-2023-08-02-09-32-11/11.mp3","time_start":32.0,"time_end":35.47},{"position":12,"content":"though we do ask that children below eight years of age are accompanied by an adult.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-6-test-2-part-1-2023-08-02-09-32-11/12.mp3","time_start":35.47,"time_end":40.3},{"position":13,"content":"Fine. That wouldn't be a problem.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-6-test-2-part-1-2023-08-02-09-32-11/13.mp3","time_start":40.69,"time_end":42.79},{"position":14,"content":"What about cost?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-6-test-2-part-1-2023-08-02-09-32-11/14.mp3","time_start":42.79,"time_end":44.43},{"position":15,"content":"Well, I think you'll find them very reasonable.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-6-test-2-part-1-2023-08-02-09-32-11/15.mp3","time_start":44.94,"time_end":48.1},{"position":16,"content":"It's £2.50 a child,","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-6-test-2-part-1-2023-08-02-09-32-11/16.mp3","time_start":48.42,"time_end":50.74},{"position":17,"content":"with 80 pence off for two or more children from the same family.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-6-test-2-part-1-2023-08-02-09-32-11/17.mp3","time_start":50.74,"time_end":54.56},{"position":18,"content":"Oh yes, very reasonable.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-6-test-2-part-1-2023-08-02-09-32-11/18.mp3","time_start":54.82,"time_end":56.95},{"position":19,"content":"And are they held in the main museum?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-6-test-2-part-1-2023-08-02-09-32-11/19.mp3","time_start":56.95,"time_end":59.68},{"position":20,"content":"Not exactly.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-